<subSubSection id="1FE5655FFFFA4177CAD1ECB2FE7C26C8" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="574036D4FFFA4177CAD1ECB2FD50259C" blockId="12.[151,1436,1502,1709]" box="[151,738,1502,1529]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFFA4177CAD1ECB2FE91259D" bold="true" box="[151,291,1502,1528]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">References:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFFA4177CB6CECB3FE01259C" author="Mbata, K. J." box="[298,435,1503,1529]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="227 - 244" refId="ref17874" refString="Mbata, K. J. (1992) Functional morphology of the stridulatory apparatus of Acanthoplus speiseri Brancsik (Orthoptera Tettigo- niidae, Hetrodinae). Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 55 (2), 227 - 244." type="journal article" year="1992">Mbata 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFFA4177CBF8ECB3FD50259C" author="Bateman, P. W. &amp; Fleming, P. A." box="[446,738,1503,1529]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="14 - 22" refId="ref15480" refString="Bateman, P. W. &amp; Fleming, P. A. (2013) Signaling or not-signaling: variation in vulnerability and defense tactics of armored ground crickets (Acanthoplus speiseri: Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae Hetrodinae). Journal of Insect Behavior, 26, 14 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10905 - 012 - 9329 - 5" type="journal article" year="2013">Bateman &amp; Fleming 2013</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFFA4177CA81EF6FFC1B2600" blockId="12.[151,1436,1502,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
Like the other species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFFA4177C81BEF6FFD662679" authorityName="Brancsik" authorityYear="1895" box="[605,724,1539,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Acanthoplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speiseri">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFFA4177C81BEF6FFD662679" box="[605,724,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">A. speiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also a quite low number of stridulatory teeth in the left file (mean 28; 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFFA4177CB57EF4BFE2E2624" author="Mbata, K. J." box="[273,412,1575,1601]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="227 - 244" refId="ref17874" refString="Mbata, K. J. (1992) Functional morphology of the stridulatory apparatus of Acanthoplus speiseri Brancsik (Orthoptera Tettigo- niidae, Hetrodinae). Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 55 (2), 227 - 244." type="journal article" year="1992">Mbata 1992</bibRefCitation>
). The calling song is described as „uninterrupted buzz similar to that of other 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFFA4177CF56EF4BFA2E2624" authority="Stal, 1873" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1873" box="[1296,1436,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Acanthoplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFFA4177CF56EF4BFA2E2624" box="[1296,1436,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Acanthoplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species“ (
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFFA4177CB45EF27FD982600" author="Bateman, P. W. &amp; Fleming, P. A." box="[259,554,1611,1637]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="14 - 22" refId="ref15480" refString="Bateman, P. W. &amp; Fleming, P. A. (2013) Signaling or not-signaling: variation in vulnerability and defense tactics of armored ground crickets (Acanthoplus speiseri: Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae Hetrodinae). Journal of Insect Behavior, 26, 14 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10905 - 012 - 9329 - 5" type="journal article" year="2013">Bateman &amp; Fleming 2013</bibRefCitation>
) without giving any detailed data.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFFA4177CA81EF02FE7C26C8" blockId="12.[151,1436,1502,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFFA4177CA81EF02FEC926ED" bold="true" box="[199,379,1646,1672]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Chromosomes:</emphasis>
The karyotype was studied by 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFFA4177C89DEF03FCCA26EC" author="Mbata, K. J." box="[731,888,1646,1673]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="142 - 145" refId="ref17919" refString="Mbata, K. J. (2005) A contribution to the cytogenetics of the armoured ground cricket, Acanthoplus speiseri (Orthoptera: Tet- tigoniidae), a pest of grain crops in Zambia. International Journal of Tropical Insect Science, 25, 142 - 145. https: // doi. org / 10.1079 / IJT 200558" type="journal article" year="2005">Mbata (2005)</bibRefCitation>
: 2n = 25 (24 + X0), FN = 26; pairs 1–12 and the X chromosome acrocentric.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
